<p> <h1>JDBC Introduction</h1>
<p>Java DataBase Connectivity is an application programming interface. It is used to connect you java programming language with the databases like SQL or ORACLE etc
JDBC API uses JDBC drivers to connect with different databases.</p>
<p><b>Application Programming Interface(API):</b>It is a collection of all classes and interfaces.API contains all features description.</p>
<p>Before JDBC we have ODBC API. ODBC API is database API to connect with databases.But ODBC uses its driver ODBC driver. This is written in c programming language.For that reason java defined its own drivers to connect with database.
<p>JDBC Drivers are written in java. JDBC have different types of drivers.</p>
 
